      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, applying the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage accumulation formulation with SST k-omega turbulence closure, produces relative hemolysis index (RH) predictions that are conservative and reproducible across the five nominated flow-speed operating points. The model is claimed to be fit for purpose in identifying the worst-case operating condition for pump-induced hemolysis under CPB surgical flow demands, meeting the RH < 1 acceptance criterion relative to the predicate device. This claim encompasses spatial convergence behaviour, boundary condition fidelity, and scalar transport accuracy for the hemolysis damage integral.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; five flow-speed combinations (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM); steady-state RANS CFD; MRL 2 assessment under ASME V&V 40-2018."
    }
  ],
